# Import Hygiene

Rules for clean, stable, and enforceable import graphs in TypeScript/Next.js projects.

## Public API only

Each feature/module folder exposes one `index.ts` as its public API. Cross-module imports must go through the entrypoint, never into internal files.

Note: See `@rules/core/code-quality-guidelines.mdc` for the canonical `index.ts` and barrel policy.

- Allowed: `import { LoginForm } from '@/features/auth'`
- Forbidden: `import { LoginForm } from '@/features/auth/ui/LoginForm'`

Enforce with `import/no-internal-modules` in ESLint.

## No wildcard re-export barrels

Do not use `export * from './...'` in entrypoints. Use explicit named re-exports so the public contract is visible and tree-shakeable.

## Consistent type imports

Use `import type` for type-only imports. Enforce with `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` set to `type-imports` with `separate-type-imports` fix style.

## No unused imports

Hard-fail on unused imports and variables. Enforce with `eslint-plugin-unused-imports`.

## No circular imports

Enforce with `import/no-cycle` (recommend `maxDepth: 1` for performance).

## Stable import ordering

Enforce with `import/first` and `import/newline-after-import`. Consider `import/order` for grouped sorting if the team prefers it.

## ESLint enforcement

See `/brp-code-quality` for the full ESLint flat config with all import hygiene rules pre-configured.
